  "description": "BCO 43-1-p. 92 Presbytery improperly ruled the complaint of Grace Presbyterian Church out of order. Rationale: The complaint was against the action of Presbytery in receiving a protest rather than the protest itself. It is proper to register a complaint against an action of presbytery. The phrase \"Here the matter shall end...\" (BCO 45-4) cited by presbytery in support of its action refers to the subject matter of a protest and not the act of receiving the protest. Adopted",
